  • Hallucination: LLMs generate plausible but incorrect information.
    → Verify LLM output independently.

  • Indirect Prompt Injection: Retrieved data and history may contain
    adversarial content designed to influence LLM behavior.
    → Validate all data sources and retrieved context.

  • Malicious Payloads: LLM output may contain harmful content
    (HTML/XSS, SQL injection, shell commands).
    → Sanitize output before rendering or execution.

  • Tool Invocation: By default, ALL tools are invoked without approval.
    → Apply tool approval patterns for sensitive operations.
    → Treat function arguments as untrusted input.


